title: Telly Bingo
overview: Telly Bingo is an Irish National Lottery draw that works like a traditional game of bingo, with a full house prize of €10,000 and the opportunity to win much more if you complete your card on or before the Snowball number is drawn. Telly Bingo was launched in 1999 and ticket holders watch the game take place every Tuesday, Thursday and Friday on television channel RTÉ One.
